nodes.title: Grid layout prompt
widgets_values: this is a character reference sheet, a grid of photographs of the same consistent character, headshots from various angles with different facial expressions. Some angles are front of, some are side profiles. In some the character looks down, or up, or to the side. The aim is to get a representataive coverage of the character from all angles.
the character is an eighteen year old woman, petite, beautiful, with long brown straight hair. Her face is cute and impish, with a slight overbite and large doe eyes.
Un-bypass to select only some images (useful for testing as speeds things up)
Depending on how well the grid is formed, you may want to detect people (connect "detect person") or just faces (connext "detect face")

Un-bypass to render in a batch rather than a list. In theory gives better consistency but you'll need a lot of VRAM*!

* 3090 with Q5 flux quant can handle a batch of 20 cells

nodes.title: Character description
widgets_values:
the character is a thirty year old female pirate captain. She has dirty blonde hair, a small scar on her cheek and wears a pirate hat. She is smudged with dirt and looks at the viewer with a haughty smirk.
